==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yaffle
<hw>Yaf"fle</hw> <pr>(y⟦acr⟧f"f'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably
imitative of its call or cry.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
European green woodpecker (<spn>Picus viridis</spn> syn. <spn>Genius
viridis</spn>). It is noted for its loud laughlike note. Called also
<altname>eccle</altname>, <altname>hewhole</altname>,
<altname>highhoe</altname>, <altname>laughing bird</altname>,
<altname>popinjay</altname>, <altname>rain bird</altname>,
<altname>yaffil</altname>, <altname>yaffler</altname>,
<altname>yaffingale</altname>, <altname>yappingale</altname>,
<altname>yackel</altname>, and <altname>woodhack</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yager</ent>⟦br⟧
